.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-encode 1  "encode " 
.SH NAME
encode \- Encode an image (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM/raw) into a WebP file
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBencode\fR <\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR> [\fB\-\-input\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-width\fR] [\fB\-\-height\fR] [\fB\-\-layout\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-method\fR] [\fB\-\-lossless\fR] [\fB\-\-lossy\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quality\fR] [\fB\-\-near\-lossless\fR] [\fB\-\-crop\fR] [\fB\-\-resize\fR] [\fB\-\-target\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-min\-psnr\fR] [\fB\-\-metadata\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Encode an image (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM/raw) into a WebP file
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output `.webp` file; `\-` writes stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-input\-format\fR \fI<INPUT_FORMAT>\fR
Input format; defaults to the extension, else the magic bytes, else raw
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
png: PNG (any color type; normalized to RGBA8)
.IP \(bu 2
ppm: Netpbm binary PPM (`P6`, RGB)
.IP \(bu 2
pam: Netpbm binary PAM (`P7`, RGBA)
.IP \(bu 2
jpeg: JPEG (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
gif: GIF (first frame as a still; whole\-file animation is a separate path)
.IP \(bu 2
tiff: TIFF (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
bmp: BMP (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
raw: Raw row\-major pixels; requires `\-\-width`/`\-\-height`/`\-\-layout`
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-width\fR \fI<WIDTH>\fR
Raw\-input width in pixels (required for raw input)
.TP
\fB\-\-height\fR \fI<HEIGHT>\fR
Raw\-input height in pixels (required for raw input)
.TP
\fB\-\-layout\fR \fI<LAYOUT>\fR [default: rgba8]
Byte order for raw input only
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
rgba8: `R, G, B, A`
.IP \(bu 2
argb8: `A, R, G, B`
.IP \(bu 2
bgra8: `B, G, R, A`
.RE
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-method\fR \fI<METHOD>\fR
Encoder effort [default: balanced, or from env/config]
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fastest: literal + subtract\-green only
.IP \(bu 2
balanced: Balanced (the default): LZ77 + color cache
.IP \(bu 2
best: Smallest: adds Tier 3 forward transforms and meta\-Huffman on top of Balanced
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-lossless\fR
Force lossless (VP8L). The default is source\-derived: JPEG → lossy, else lossless
.TP
\fB\-\-lossy\fR
Encode lossily (VP8) instead of losslessly (VP8L)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quality\fR \fI<QUALITY>\fR
Lossy quality 0\-100 (higher = larger, closer to source); selects \-\-lossy
.TP
\fB\-\-near\-lossless\fR \fI<N>\fR
Near\-lossless preprocessing 0\-100 (lower = stronger; implies lossless)
.TP
\fB\-\-crop\fR \fI<X,Y,W,H>\fR
Crop before encoding: `x,y,width,height` in pixels (applied before \-\-resize)
.TP
\fB\-\-resize\fR \fI<WxH>\fR
Resize before encoding: `WxH` (use 0 on one axis to keep aspect)
.TP
\fB\-\-target\-size\fR \fI<SIZE>\fR
Target output size, e.g. `200k` or `2M`, found by searching lossy quality.

Lossy only: it bisects quality until the encoded file fits. With `\-v`, the search is printed. Cannot combine with `\-\-lossless`.
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-psnr\fR \fI<DB>\fR
Target reconstruction PSNR floor in dB (lossy only; pairs with \-\-target\-size)
.TP
\fB\-\-metadata\fR \fI<METADATA>\fR
Metadata to embed: all,none,icc,exif,xmp (default: all — kinder than cwebp)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
all: Keep ICC, Exif, and XMP
.IP \(bu 2
none: Strip everything (a bare `VP8L` output)
.IP \(bu 2
icc: Keep the ICC color profile
.IP \(bu 2
exif: Keep Exif
.IP \(bu 2
xmp: Keep XMP
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fIINPUT\fR] [default: \-]
Input image (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM/raw); `\-` (default) reads stdin
